
                                                                  

# LIFEFRAME v2 — Your Life, Mastered

LIFEFRAME v2 is an **AI-powered personal dashboard** designed to unify multiple aspects of life—productivity, academics, habits, health, and planning—into a single, highly interactive interface.

This project is currently **under active development**.

---

## 🚧 Project Status

> Ongoing — features are being actively built and refined
> AI integrations (via Claude) are experimental and evolving

---

## 🧠 Core Idea

LIFEFRAME aims to function as a **centralized life operating system**, combining:

* Task management
* Habit tracking
* Academic performance monitoring
* Calendar & scheduling
* AI-assisted insights

---

## ✨ Features (Implemented / In Progress)

### 🧭 Dashboard

* Real-time overview of:

  * Tasks
  * Habit streaks
  * Study metrics
  * GPA tracking
* Smart AI insights panel

### ✅ Task Management

* Add / toggle tasks
* Categorization (Study, Health, Finance, Personal)
* Daily tracking

### 🔥 Habit Tracker

* Weekly habit visualization
* Streak tracking system
* Interactive completion toggles

### 📅 Calendar System

* Monthly and weekly views
* Event creation with categories:

  * Study
  * Exams
  * Health
  * Social
  * Tasks

### 🎓 Student HQ

* Subject-wise performance tracking
* GPA visualization
* Assignment tracking
* Semester timeline (weeks, exams, holidays)

### 🤖 AI Features (Claude-powered)

* Smart insights (contextual suggestions)
* Notes & summarization (UI scaffold present)
* Performance prediction (UI-level implementation)

### 🎨 UI/UX System

* Multi-theme support:

  * Midnight (default)
  * Aurora
  * Sand
  * Obsidian
  * Forest
  * Rose
* Customization:

  * Accent colors
  * Typography
  * Layout density
  * Sidebar width

### 🔐 Authentication (Frontend Mock)

* Login / Signup UI
* Avatar selection
* Demo (guest) mode

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

### Frontend

* HTML5
* CSS3 (custom design system with variables)
* Vanilla JavaScript

### Design System

* Custom theme engine using CSS variables
* Responsive grid layouts
* Component-based UI (cards, modals, panels)

### AI Integration

* Claude (used conceptually / partially integrated)

---

## 📂 Project Structure (Current)

```
lifeframe-v2.html   # Main application (monolithic frontend)
```

> Note: The project is currently a **single-page monolithic file**, not modularized yet.

---

## ⚙️ How to Run

1. Download or clone the project
2. Open the HTML file in a browser:

```bash
open lifeframe-v2.html
```

No server or build tools required.

---

## 🚀 Planned Improvements

* Backend integration (Django / Supabase)
* Persistent data storage
* Full AI integration (real API calls)
* Modular architecture (React or component split)
* Authentication (real system)
* Mobile responsiveness improvements
* API-based integrations (Spotify, calendars, etc.)

---

## ⚠️ Limitations

* No database (data is not persistent)
* AI features are mostly UI-level placeholders
* Authentication is simulated
* Single-file architecture (not scalable yet)

---

## 🧩 Vision

The long-term goal is to evolve LIFEFRAME into:

> A fully intelligent, adaptive system that understands user behavior and actively optimizes life decisions using AI.

---

## 🤝 Contribution

Currently not open for contributions (early-stage project), but structure will be improved for collaboration later.

---

## 📌 Author Notes

* This is a **self-driven experimental project**
* Focus is on **UI systems + AI-driven workflows**
* Built with iterative prototyping approach

